OL,3,CNew health boss wants to leave Jersey
OL,4,Cwith a 'world-class health service'
OL,6,FMr Hayhoe continued: "It's not so much
OL,7,Fcost-cutting as making sure we're
OL,8,Fusing the taxpayer's money in Jersey
OL,9,Fto deliver the maximum amount of care
OL,10,Fwhich is the kind of currency of this."
OL,12,FThe Board's new Chair has over 35
OL,13,Fyears of experience in health and
OL,14,Fsocial care leadership, working as the
OL,15,FChair within a range of contexts
OL,16,Fincluding the NHS.
OL,18,FMr Hayhoe says: "I want to leave
OL,19,FJersey with a real world-class health
OL,20,Fservice by the end of my time here.
